# Object-Oriented Programming Project (Python)

## Project Overview
This project was developed as part of a Programming Fundamentals course. The objective was to design and implement a Python program capable of solving a non-trivial problem using object-oriented programming principles.

The project demonstrates the ability to structure a program using classes, methods, and modular components to build a functional application.

## Key Concepts Demonstrated
- Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
- Class and object design
- Method implementation
- Program modularization
- Debugging and testing
- Code documentation

## Technologies Used
- Python

## Features
- Designed multiple classes to represent components of the system
- Implemented methods to perform specific operations
- Applied problem-solving and program design principles
- Structured code following Python programming conventions

## Learning Outcomes
Through this project, I gained practical experience in designing structured programs using object-oriented programming techniques and translating problem requirements into functional Python code.

